cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel architecture for sequence-to-sequence learning, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions that the architecture can be trained with back-propagation, which suggests that it falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses stacked layers of memories and read-write operations, which are common in neural network architectures, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions machine translation, which is a common application in NLP, and the architecture can be applied to CV tasks as well, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
